tldr: The user requested to implement a database, an admin dashboard, and
  authentication for a sleep questionnaire application based on a Statement of
  Work. The solution involved setting up a PostgreSQL database with Prisma,
  creating API routes for data storage and retrieval, and building a simple
  admin dashboard protected by Next.js middleware.
overview: The user's intent was to enhance a sleep questionnaire application by
  adding persistent data storage and an administrative interface. The approach
  involved integrating a PostgreSQL database (NeonDB) via Prisma to store
  questionnaire responses, including denormalized demographic data for easy
  access. An API was developed to handle the submission, retrieval, and CSV
  export of these responses. For client access, a simple admin dashboard was
  created, protected by a lightweight authentication system using Next.js
  middleware and a basic session cookie. Initial custom session management was
  later simplified to leverage Next.js middleware for cleaner route protection.
  The implementation also included updating the questionnaire's demographic
  fields and integrating the form submission with the new API. Extensive testing
  confirmed the functionality of the database, API endpoints, authentication,
  and dashboard.
